","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Standish","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name from Standish (Lancashire, now part of Greater Manchester), from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>edisc</i> ‘enclosure, enclosed park’. Standish (Gloucestershire) does not appear to have contributed towards the surname.","History: Myles Standish (<i>c.</i> 1584–1656) was a soldier of fortune, from 1620 captain of the <i>Mayflower</i> Pilgrims at Plymouth Colony. Little is known of his origins and early life, but in his will he claimed to be descended from a leading Catholic family, the Standishes of Standish, Lancashire, England. He also claimed to have been deprived of his inheritance, a claim not confirmed."],"variants":[{"name":"Standage","meanings":["English:","probably a variant of   Standish  .","in Leicestershire and Buckinghamshire, the name may alternatively be from Stanedge Grange in Hartington Nether Quarter or Stanage End in Outseats (both Derbyshire); but evidence is needed for this. The placenames derive from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>ecg</i> ‘edge, escarpment’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Standish was born in 1347. She had at least 1 son with Sir John III de Ashton , Lord, Knight, Military Commander, MP. She died in 1415, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428"},"fi":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428"},"fr":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428","lifeSummary":"Alice Standish est née en 1347. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir John III de Ashton , Lord, Knight, Military Commander, MP. Elle est décédée en 1415, à l’âge de 68 ans."},"de":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428","lifeSummary":"Alice Standish wurde 1347 geboren. Sie hatte mit Sir John III de Ashton , Lord, Knight, Military Commander, MP mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1415 im Alter von 68 Jahren."},"ht":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428"},"hu":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428"},"id":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428"},"it":{"1347–1415":"1347–1415","1344–1398":"1344–1398","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1415":"1415","1347":"1347","1368":"1368","1344":"1344","1398":"1398","1428":"1428","life